{
  "texts": [
    "There is no such thing as indirect experience --there is only direct experience or words (i.e., verbal descriptions).",
    "Direct Experience: This involves firsthand, sensorimotor interactions with the world.",
    "Direct experiences are the foundation of knowledge and understanding for humans, providing the sensory and contextual basis for learning and cognition.",
    "IVG pertains to learning and understanding concepts through verbal descriptions, explanations, or narratives.",
    "It does not involve direct sensorimotor experience with the referents of these descriptions."
  ]
}